ity Co-op", "Cooperative Student Housing", "Cooperative Housing Committee", "Cooperative Housing Focus Group", "Concordia Student Congress", "Survey", "Campaigns", "Campaigns", "Unpaid Internships", "Climate Justice & Divestment", "Anti-Consumerism", "Past Campaigns", "#BringBissanHome", "Austerity", "International Tuition Hike", "Tribunals", "Student Life", "Fee Levy Groups", "Student Groups & Associations", "Bursaries at the CSU", "Sustainability", "Food Systems Reform", "Sustainability Resources on Campus", "Food System Special Project Funding Policy", "Clubs", "Active Clubs", "Starting a New Club", "How to Manage your Club", "Resources", "Apply for Funding", "Apply for Funding", "Special Project Funding", "CSU Special Clubs Funding", "CSU Community Action Fund", "Food Systems Special Project Funding", "CSU Committee Funding", "Other Sources of Funding", "Home", "\u203a", "Services", "CSU Live Newsletter", "What is it?", "The CSU LIVE is one of the Concordia Student Union's communications initiatives to help keep Concordia students in the loop.\u00a0CSU LIVE is a weekly\u00a0newsletter that includes up-to-date campus activities & initiatives, contests, job offerings & more.", "Our other communications\u00a0initiatives\u00a0include our\u00a0Facebook, Twitter, Instagram, and YouTube pages.", "Who receives the CSU LIVE?", "The CSU LIVE newsletter is sent weekly to all undergraduates by e-mail. To follow the Concordia Student Union's other communications initiatives, click on our social media links below.", "For submissions to the CSU LIVE newsletter, please contact", "communications@csu.qc.ca", "Social Media", "Interested in following your union? Subscribe, follow, like, and we\u2019ll keep you updated with news on the CSU\u2019s events & campaigns!", "facebook.com/csu.qc.ca", "twitter.com/csumtl", "instagram.com/csumtl", "Contact", "Send your requests & questions to the CSU's Communications Coordinator.", "communications@csu.qc.ca", "| 514-848-7474 ext. 7892", "Not receiving the newsletter?\nWe receive our undergraduate student list after the drop deadline of every academic term and update our mailing list accordingly. If you want to receive the newsletter at a different email address than that which you used to register at Concordia, then please contact us at commscoordinator@csu.qc.ca\n\nAfter each semester our mailing list is updated once again, so if you want to avoid having to contact us to update your email every semester, then please update your primary email address via the myconcordia.ca portal.\n\nYou could also sign up your new email using the form below, but keep in mind that your registration will only be valid for the semester in questions as the content of our newsletters are intended for Concordia undergraduate students exclusively.", "<!--/*--><![CDATA[/* ><!--*/\n#mc_embed_signup{background:#fff; clear:left; font:14px Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif; }\n\t/* Add your own MailChimp form style overrides in your site stylesheet or in this style block.\n\t   We recommend moving this block and the preceding CSS link to the HEAD of your HTML file. */\n\n/*--><!]]>*/", "Subscribe to CSU Live", "\u200b", "Quick Links", "Login", "Resources", "Jobs", "Contact Information", "Downtown:\u00a01455 de Maisonneuve Blvd West,\u00a0H-711\u00a0Montr\u00e9al, QC H3G 1M8", "Loyola:\u00a07141 Sherbrooke Street West, CC-426\u00a0Montr\u00e9al,\u00a0QC\u00a0H4B 1R6", "Phone -\u00a0514 848-7474 | Fax: 514 848-7450", "Email -", "contactus@csu.qc.ca", "Concordia Student Union | Copyright 2016\u00a0|\u00a0All Rights Reserved"]}
