lations", "Our team", "News releases", "Find an expert", "Ask our experts", "Op-eds", "Media kits", "Spotlights", "The Campaign for Concordia", "Study resources", "Calendar - Graduate", "Calendar - Undergraduate", "Class schedules", "Class cancellations", "Course registration", "Important academic dates", "More academic resources", "Campus services", "Concordia Stores", "IT services", "Job opportunities", "Security", "Shuttle bus", "Student Service Centre (Birks)", "All campus services", "What's new", "Calendar of events", "Latest news", "Media Relations", "Faculties, Schools & Colleges", "Arts and Science", "Engineering and Computer Science", "Fine Arts", "John Molson School of Business", "School of Graduate Studies", "All Schools, Colleges & Departments", "Quick links", "Webmail", "Library", "Cspace", "Study resources", "Calendar - Graduate", "Calendar - Undergraduate", "Class schedules", "Class cancellations", "Course registration", "Important academic dates", "More academic resources", "Campus services", "Concordia Stores", "IT services", "Job opportunities", "Security", "Shuttle bus", "Student Service Centre (Birks)", "All campus services", "What's new", "Calendar of events", "Latest news", "Media Relations", "Faculties, Schools & Colleges", "Arts and Science", "Engineering and Computer Science", "Fine Arts", "John Molson School of Business", "School of Graduate Studies", "All Schools, Colleges & Departments", "Information for...", "Future students", "Student hub", "Alumni & friends", "Parents", "Faculty & staff", "Media", "Concordia", "Directories", "Search", "Concordia University", "News", "Concordia.ca", "/", "News", "/", "Media Relations", "/", "Ask our experts", "Facebook", "Twitter", "LinkedIn", "GooglePlus", "Ask our experts", "Each week, we feature Concordia faculty and staff who are ready to provide expert opinion, comment and analysis on today's headlines. Remember an expert you would like to contact about a past news topic?", "Search our topics archive", ",", "browse our experts database", ", or", "contact a member of our team", "for support.", "News topics as of April 10, 2017", "Bombings in Egypt", "At least 44 people were killed and another 100 were wounded on Sunday, April 9 when Coptic churches were the targets of bombings in two Egyptian cities. The Islamic State has claimed responsibility for both attacks. Kyle Matthews, executive director of the Montreal Institute for Genocide and Human Rights Studies (MIGS), and Andr\u00e9 Gagn\u00e9, associate professor in the Department of Theological Studies, can provide perspective on the weekend violence.", "Andr\u00e9 Gagn\u00e9, associate professor, Department of Theological Studies", "Cell:\u00a0514-999-4188", "Andre.gagne@concordia.ca", "Kyle Matthews, executive director, MIGS", "Cell: 514-975-8160", "Kyle.matthews@concordia.ca", "Bombardier Salary Hikes", "Public protests continue to decry Bombardier\u2019s decision to generously increase compensation packages for its executives after receiving close to $1,5 billion from the federal and provincial governments. Isabelle Dostaler, an expert on the aerospace industry in the John Molson School of Business JMSB, can look at the current context of Bombardier\u2019s operations.", "Isabelle Dostaler, professor, Department of Management, JMSB", "514-848-2424 ext. 2798", "idostaler@jmsb.concordia.ca", "Controversies surrounding Canada\u2019s 150", "th", "anniversary", "The celebration of Canada\u2019s 150", "th", "anniversary is unfolding in the midst of a series of controversies over how to best remember history. Political leaders in Quebec and Nova Scotia are criticising the CBC television series The Story of Us, for its negative depiction of francophone historical figures as well as its omission of significant events. Meanwhile, the Bank of Canada has unveiled the design for a new ten dollar bill that will feature its selection of prominent Canadians. Ronald Rudin, professor in the Department of History and co-director of the Centre for Oral History and Digital Storytelling, can address the challenges in mounting inclusive historical commemorations.", "Ronald Rudin, \u00a0professor, Department of History & co-director, Centre for Oral History and Digital Storytelling", "514-848-2424 ext. 2428", "Ronald.rudin@concordia.ca", "Anniversary of the U.S. Civil Rights Act", "\u201cAs the U.S. Supreme Court has scaled back some of the hard won victories of the 1960s\u2019 civil rights movement, and President Trump has voiced antipathy to the views of Black Lives Matter advocates, odds are that civil rights controversies will be back in the headlines before long.\u201d", "Graham Dodds on the anniversary of the introduction of the Civil Rights Act in the U.S.", "Graham Dodds, associate professor, Department of Political Science", "514-848-2424 ext. 5605", "g.dodds@concordia.ca", "Seach past topics", "Media Relations", "Our team", "Mary-Jo Barr", "Fiona Downey", "Nadia Kherif", "Michael Watkins", "News releases", "Find an expert", "Ask our experts", "Op-eds", "Media kits", "Zone \u00c9ducation-Culture \u2013 Rue Bishop", "Concordia's new look for varsity sports", "Engineering Sustainable Growth featuring the Bloodhound SSC", "Grey Nuns Student Residence and Reading Room", "Ed Meagher Arena", "Spotlights", "Spotlight on Montreal Infrastructure", "Join the conversation", "Follow @ConcordiaUnews", "Back to top", "\u00a9 Concordia University", "Concordia University", "- Call us at 514-848-2424", "About", "Academics", "Admissions", "Campus life", "Research", "International", "Future students", "Current students", "Alumni & friends", "Parents", "Faculty & staff", "Media", "Sir George Williams Campus", "1455 De Maisonneuve Blvd. W.", "Montreal", ",", "Quebec", ",", "Canada", "H3G 1M8", "See SGW Campus map", "Loyola Campus", "7141 Sherbrooke Street W.", "Montreal", ",", "Quebec", ",", "Canada", "H4B 1R6", "See Loyola Campus map", "facebook", "twitter", "google", "youtube", "linkedin", "pinterest"