{"name": ["http://www.cupfa.org/events/"], "content": ["Events | CUPFA", "Skip to content", "Professional Development", "Deadlines", "Teaching Application Form", "News", "Quick Links:", "Science Cafe on PKD with Dr. CHIARA GAMBERA", "Posted on", "October 22, 2017", "For more information, and to RSVP, go to: http://www.endpkd.ca/sciencecafe2017", "Continue reading", "ADRIAN NORVID Perfomance, FOFA Gallery, Oct. 19 & 20, 4pm", "Posted on", "October 16, 2017", "The Little Black Bumhole Opera Presents Adrian Norvid Performing as Lord Muck In Opus Chokeus A dark as molasses sonic exploration of Parlance, Utterance and Vehemence, including: the varieties of Scottish Shortbread and the laying waste of a perfectly good \u2026", "Continue reading", "Cinema Event Co-Organized by MARY ELLEN DAVIS", "Posted on", "September 2, 2017", "Continue reading", "Exhibition by FRANCINE POTVIN", "Posted on", "September 2, 2017", "Continue reading", "MEET AND GREET \u2013 Thursday, August 31", "Posted on", "August 16, 2017", "Irish Embassy Pub 1234 Bishop Street Thursday, August 31, 4:45 \u2013 7:30 pm", "Continue reading", "BONNIE BAXTER receives 2017 President\u2019s Excellence in Teaching Award", "Posted on", "June 4, 2017", "The President\u2019s Excellence in Teaching Award recognizes sustained excellence in teaching as characterized by high academic quality, social responsibility, innovation in teaching, outstanding student experience, outstanding student engagement, and community engagement.\u00a0Thank you, Bonnie, for raising our membership\u2019s profile with your \u2026", "Continue reading", "Variations \u2013 an exhibition by SUSAN S. SCOTT", "Posted on", "May 31, 2017", "June 1 \u2013 July 22, 2017 The artist will be present on Saturday July 8. 5432 Boulevard St-Laurent,\u00a0Montreal H2T 1S1 Wednesday through Saturday, noon to 4 pm", "Continue reading", "Feature article on Dr. CHIARA GAMBERI\u2019s groundbreaking research on kidney disease", "Posted on", "May 25, 2017", "\u201cRevealed: The Biochemical Pathways of Kidney Disease,\u201d The Concordian", "Continue reading", "Dr. IMAN GOHAR and Dr. PANKAJ KAMTHAN win Excellence in Teaching Awards \u2013 Faculty of Engineering and Computer Science", "Posted on", "May 23, 2017", "Photos: Laurel Leduc", "Continue reading", "FRANCINE POTVIN to participate in Canada C3", "Posted on", "May 5, 2017", "Studio Arts professor Francine Potvin is one of 15 artists chosen for Canada C3, a 15-step adventure to celebrate\u00a0the 150th anniversary of Canadian confederation. Francine will participate in Step 6, from Nain to Iqaluit. We\u2019ll keep you posted! For more \u2026", "Continue reading", "Robert Holland Murray (1939-2017)", "Posted on", "May 2, 2017", "It is with great sadness that we announce the passing of Professor Robert Holland Murray, retired part-time faculty member in Painting & Drawing/Studio Arts, on April 21st, 2017. The funeral service will take place on Thursday, May 4th, 2017 at \u2026", "Continue reading", "DONATO TOTARO wins 2017 Distinguished Teaching Award \u2013 Faculty of Fine Arts", "Posted on", "April 28, 2017", "Quoting the Faculty of Fine Arts web page: \u201cAn award is being granted by the Faculty of Fine Arts, in recognition of Dr. Totaro\u2019s long-time commitment to Concordia\u2019s Film Studies programme, his generosity with students, his out-reach to the Montreal \u2026", "Continue reading", "ART FILM \u201cINQUIRY INTO TIME AND PERCEPTION, STUDY #1\u201d FRIDAY MARCH 24TH, 2017 AT 6PM", "Posted on", "March 21, 2017", "Philip Szporer\u2019s projection-installation, \u201cInquiry Into Time and Perception, Study #1,\u201d with choreography by Mariko Tanabe, and featuring Mariko and Rachel Harris, and camerawork by Bill Kerrigan, will have its Montreal premiere at the Festival international du film sur l\u2019art/International Festival \u2026", "Continue reading", "CUPFA MICROLINK WORKSHOP \u201cCOMMUNITY OUTREACH AND PUBLIC INTERVENTION\u201d FRIDAY MARCH 17TH, 2017 AT 5PM", "Posted on", "March 10, 2017", "Date:\u00a0Friday March 17th, 2017\u00a0 Time: 5:00\u00a0to 7:00 PM Location:\u00a0EV building, room 6.735, 1515 Ste. Catherine West The following faculty will present their research: Erik Chevrier (Psychology), Caroline Laurin-Beaucage (Contemporary Dance), Jenny Lin (Print Media), Pata Macedo (Design and Computation Arts), \u2026", "Continue reading", "\u2018CHOEUR MAHA\u2019 PERFORMS ON WEDNESDAY MARCH 8TH, 2017", "Posted on", "March 6, 2017", "To commemorate International Women\u2019s Day on\u00a0Wednesday March 8th, 2017, Montreal-based choir\u00a0Choeur Maha\u00a0will\u00a0\u00a0perform three sets over the lunch hour. \u00a0Founded and directed by longtime part-time faculty member Kathy Kennedy, the choir have been performing in the Montreal area and beyond since \u2026", "Continue reading", "Home", "About", "Mandate & History", "Executive 2017-20", "Committees", "Staff", "News & Events", "News", "Events", "Videos", "Media Coverage \u2013 Negotiations", "Collective Agreement", "Pensions and Retirement", "Pension Information", "Retirement Planning", "Professional Development", "About PD", "CUPFA Grants", "Travel and Expenses", "Grant Reports", "Small Claims", "PD \u2013 FAQ", "Office of Research", "Forms", "Publications", "Newsletters", "Survival Guide", "Commandments", "Multi-Section Courses", "Concordia Resources", "FAQ", "Contact Us", "Search for:", "Recent Posts", "Official Signing of 5th Collective Agreement", "Words and Public Space, Andrew Forster, Erin Moure...", "Campus Equity Week article in The Concordian", "Instability of Work a Cause of Stress for...", "BONNIE BAXTER wins Charles-Biddle Award 2017", "Post Archives", "Post Archives", "Select Month", "November 2017", "October 2017", "September 2017", "August 2017", "July 2017", "June 2017", "May 2017", "April 2017", "March 2017", "February 2017", "January 2017", "December 2016", "November 2016", "October 2016", "September 2016", "August 2016", "June 2016", "May