s", "MF", "ETF", "Show More", "CREATE PORTFOLIO", "ADD INVESTMENT", "Download ET MARKETS APP", "Get ET Markets in your own language", "DOWNLOAD THE APP NOW", "+91", "CHOOSE LANGUAGE", "ENG", "ENG - English", "HIN - \u0939\u093f\u0928\u094d\u0926\u0940", "GUJ - \u0a97\u0ac1\u0a9c\u0ab0\u0abe\u0aa4\u0ac0", "MAR - \u092e\u0930\u093e\u0920\u0940", "BEN - \u09ac\u09be\u0982\u09b2\u09be", "KAN - \u0c95\u0ca8\u0ccd\u0ca8\u0ca1", "ORI - \u0b13\u0b21\u0b3f\u0b06", "TEL - \u0c24\u0c46\u0c32\u0c41\u0c17\u0c41", "TAM - \u0ba4\u0bae\u0bbf\u0bb4\u0bcd", "Drag according to your convenience", "ET NOW RADIO", "ET NOW", "TIMES NOW", "Digg", "Google Bookmarks", "StumbleUpon", "Reddit", "Newsvine", "Live Bookmarks", "Technorati", "Yahoo Bookmarks", "Blogmarks", "Del.icio.us", "ApnaCircle", "Google Plus", "Pinterest", "Russia considering to offer e-visas for Indian tourists travelling in group: Minister", "By", "Dipanjan Roy Chaudhury", ", ET Bureau", "|", "Updated: Nov 11, 2017, 12.57 AM IST", "0", "Comments", "Emphasising on Indo-Russian co-production of movies the Minister said that an Inter-Governmental Agreement for co-production will be signed by the two countries.", "NEW DELHI:", "Russia", "is considering to offer e-visas to Indian tourists travelling in a group eyeing to increase quantum of tourists from here and thereby deepen people-to-people contacts, informed Russian Minister of Culture and Tourism", "Vladimir Medinsky", ".", "\u201cThe quantum of Indian tourists travelling to Russia and vice versa is still low. After Russia introduced group", "e-visa", "for South Koreans tourist flow increased by 70 per cent in one year,\u201d Medinsky told ET in an exclusive interaction following his meeting here on Friday.", "Currently 2,00,000 Russian tourists travel to India on an average and 70,000 Indian tourists travel to Russia on an average annually. \u201cThere is a huge potential to increase this quantum and push Indo-Russian people-to-people ties,\u201d pointed the visiting Minister who is also visiting India with regard to screening of popular Russian movies across Indian cities \u2013 Delhi, Mumbai and Kolkata.", "Hoping to bring back glory of cultural ties that existed between India and erstwhile", "Soviet Union", ", Medinsky informed that a film production will be launched by Russia titled \u2018Travelling into India\u2019 to showcase India to the international community at large. Similar productions have done in the past \u2013 \u2018Travelling into India\u2019 & \u2018Traveling into China\u2019.", "Emphasising on Indo-Russian co-production of movies the Minister said that an Inter-Governmental Agreement for co-production will be signed by the two countries.", "The Russian Minister held delegation level talks with MoS Culture (Independent Charge)", "Mahesh Sharma", "here on Friday. \"'Had a fruitful meeting with the Minister of Culture of the Russian Federation, Mr. Vladimir Medinsky @medinskiy_vr and discussed number of topics including co-production in the cinema, increasing people to people contact between two countries etc,\" tweeted Sharma after the meeting.", "The third edition of Russian Film Days, an initiative to strengthen the Indo-Russian relationship through cinematic and cultural exchange, began here with a special tribute to Raj Kapoor. The film festival opened at Siri Fort Auditorium with a theatrical performance dedicated to", "Raj Kapoor", "and his legendary film of the 1970 year, \"Mera Naam Joker\", which remains one of the most favourite Indian movies in Russia.", "The festival opened with director Valery Todorovsky's dance drama The Bolshoi, that shows a young ballerina's struggle to perform at Bolshoi theatre. During the festival over the course of three days, Delhi movie-goers will be able to watch 'The Bolshoi' at Siri Fort Auditorium, 'The Ghost of Sonora', 'Yana + Yanko', 'Kitchen: World chef battle', and 'Attraction' at DT Cinemas in Saket.", "0", "Comments", "Read more on", "Vladimir Medinsky", "Soviet Unio