{"name": ["http://punemirror.indiatimes.com/others/you/Dermatologists-Donts/articleshow/60860133.cms"], "content": ["Dermatologists\u2019 Don\u2019ts - Pune Mirror", "Pune Mirror", "Ad Blocker Detected", "We have noticed that you have an ad blocker enabled which restricts ads served on the site.", "Please disable it to continue reading", "Pune Mirror", "Steps for disabling ad blocker", "Home", "Steps for disabling ad blocker", "Refresh", "WELCOME,", "My Times", "LOGOUT", "SIGN IN", "Mumbai Mirror", "|", "Bangalore Mirror", "|", "Ahmedabad Mirror", "Home", "Pune", "Pune Speaks", "Cover Story", "Crime", "Civic", "Others", "Campus", "Entertainment", "Bollywood", "Hollywood", "Film Reviews", "Unwind", "Marathi Reviews", "Columns", "Aside", "The Informer", "Talk Back", "Columnists", "News", "India", "World", "Sports", "Cricket", "Others", "Photos", "Entertainment", "Sports", "News", "Cartoon & Kidzone", "Videos", "Cricbuzz", "Travel", "All", "Leisure", "Sunday Read", "Scitech", "You", "Special", "Eat", "Home", "Others", "You", "Dermatologists\u2019 Don\u2019ts", "By\u00a0ARUNA RATHOD PANVEL", "ARUNA RATHOD PANVEL", "|", "Updated: Sep 28, 2017, 02.30 AM IST", "Print this article", "Reduce font size", "Increase font size", "My Saved articles", "Whatsapp", "Facebook", "Google Plus", "Twitter", "Email", "Linkedin", "SMS", "Share", "Whatsapp", "Facebook", "Google Plus", "Twitter", "Email", "Linkedin", "SMS", "(top) DrRashmi Shetty says abrasive exfoliating scrubs may cause pigmentation;  (inset) Reversing some skin damage may require both medical products and aesthetic treatments; (Below) For facial hair, laser hair removal is a better alternative than waxing", "You know you\u2019re on the right track when you\u2019re following in an expert\u2019s footsteps, so take your cue from these top skincare experts and avoid these", "Sure, the well-meaning aunty in your building has a thousand ideas about what you can do to get rid of your acne, but do the sun spots on her face or the rash on her arms offer evidence of her expertise in the subject? You know there\u2019s only one pro who actually knows the secret to good skin: the dermatologist. She or he has studied the subject for years, and you can bet that she or he would have tried and tested all sorts of treatments, whether these have to do with skin, hair or nails. So, when dermatologists stay away from a product or process, you know you\u2019d be wise to do so too. Here\u2019s a list of what to avoid:", "EXFOLIATING SCRUBS", "Here\u2019s why:", "Dr Rashmi Shetty, aesthetic dermatologist, Ra Skin and Aesthetics, explains, \u201cThe skin is soft and delicate, hence should be treated carefully. Using a \u2018scrub\u2019 may lead to micro abrasions, that may cause a micro inflammation, which will in turn lead to pigmentation.\u201d She explains that some exfoliation products and oldfashioned scrubs with large, granules are what ought to be avoided, \u201cbut exfoliation itself isn\u2019t bad for you. Ideally, it should be done in the night time, as the process removes dead skin, leaving your skin most receptive to damage, and it\u2019s best not to expose it to the elements (like sunlight) in that state. Use a nourishing cream after a gentle exfoliator at night time for maximum benefit.\u201d", "Instead:", "\u201cUse a gentle face wash which comes with exfoliating beads in it, and ensure it\u2019s manufactured by a reputed company. For a natural alternative, use a blend of sugar and honey,\u201d says Dr Shetty. She adds that one should limit exfoliation to once a week, \u201cunless very sure about how gentle the product you\u2019re using is on the skin.\u201d", "SKIN LIGHTENING CREAMS", "Here\u2019s why:", "\u201cI would never use skin lightening creams which contain cortisone and hydroquinone,\u201d says Dr Jaishree Sharad, CEO, Skinfiniti Aesthetic and Laser Clinic, referring to applications which are sometimes used to treat age spots and skin discolouration, \u201cas these could have harmful effects.\u201d She explains, \u201cThey make the skin thin, sensitive and sometimes you may have rebound pigmentation or acne breakouts. \u201cSkin lightening products with fluocinolone or mometasone are particularly harmful,\u201d adds Dr Sharad.", "Instead:", "\u201cYou may use Vitamin C serums, curcumin or turmeric-based creams or creams containing arbutin and liquorice,\u201d she says.", "POPPING ZITS", "Here\u2019s why:", "\u201cWhen one pops a pimple, there is damage to the skin which leads to hyperpigmentation (darkening) and the likelihood of scarring. Many apply toothpaste, garlic or neem on pimples, believing that these would reduce the inflammation, but in some cases using such items may lead to skin irritation and inflammation. They may even cause a superficial burn,\u201d says dermatologist Dr Zubin Mandlewala of Reflectionz Clinic.", "Instead:", "\u201cConsult a doctor, so he or she may assess the root cause of the acne. This could be hormonal, caused by some cosmetics or because of the consumption of high glycaemic foods, or one\u2019s occupation and lifestyle may even be what\u2019s at the root of the problem,\u201d says Dr Mandlewala. Acne can be of two types: noninflammatory (white heads and black heads) and inflammatory (red and/or pus-filled pimples). \u201cDepending on the type, it must be treated with topical creams, gels, oral medications, and, if necessary, certain procedures,\u201d says Dr Mandlewala.", "OTC FUNGAL INFECTION CREAMS", "Here\u2019s why:", "Dermatologist Dr Gayatri Bharadwaj explains, \u201cFungal infections typically manifest as an itchy rash, generally in the folds of the skin. Most people are not aware of the dangers of using OTC creams to treat these and are desperate for instant relief. But, many such products contain steroids that damage the skin and/ or cause thinning of the skin, redness, acne, scars and stretch marks. Besides, superficial blood vessels become visible with prolonged use of these. And, furthermore, long-term use may cause serious side-effects like kidney damage, growth retardation in children, bone loss, swelling of the body, diabetes, depression, psychosis and memory loss,\u201d she says. And, for all that, these don\u2019t even cure fungal infections; the problem will resurface as soon as the treatment is discontinued.", "Instead:", "\u201cOpt for proper antifungal creams or oral medication, which should be prescribed by a qualified dermatologist. And, preventive measures help, for example, keep the affected area totally dry and wear loose cotton clothes as sweating worsens this condition,\u201d says Dr Bharadwaj.", "WAXING FACIAL HAIR", "Here\u2019s why:", "\u201cWaxing the face can damage the epidermis and may cause hair follicles to get infected (folliculitis). Also, repeated waxing can cause the skin to turn dark,\u201d says skin specialist Dr Rasya Dixit.", "Instead:", "\u201cThough expensive, laser hair removal is a good alternative, as the laser only affects the hair and doesn\u2019t damage the skin,\u201d she says.", "HAIR-REMOVAL TECHNIQUES FOR GIRLS", "Here\u2019s why:", "Many girls under the age of 10 years complain of excessive hair growth these days. \u201cHowever, laser hair removal treatments or any other hair removal techniques are pointless at this time. For one thing, the skin is too delicate. Besides, post puberty there will be a change in the hair cycle, so even if the girl has gone through a laser treatment, the hair will grow back. Besides, if the child has any hormonal imbalance, the hair may grow back thicker,\u201d warns Dr Krupa Amonkar, consulting dermatologist, Palkar\u2019s Polyclinic.", "Instead:", "If your daughter is adamant about having hair removal treatments, \u201cyou may reduce the frequency of these by using solutions to reduce hair growth, such as eflonithin creams. These prolong the hair cycle, i.e. the hair takes longer to grow back,\u201d says Dr Amonkar.", "ANTI-AGEING CREAMS", "Here\u2019s why:", "Ageing skin is the result of multiple factors \u2014 constant, cumulative sun exposure, an erratic lifestyle and genetics are some of these. Due to these, collagen and elastin get depleted from the deeper layers of skin and this causes signs of ageing like wrinkles, open pores and coarse, rough skin. \u201cThe idea that a topical anti-ageing cream will correct these issues that arise due to problems that run far deeper, has no basis in logic,\u201d says Dr Madhuri Agarwal, founder and medical director of Yavana Aesthetics Clinic.", "Instead:", "\u201cIdeally, to keep your skin looking young and supple for longer, it is advised to start a healthy skin care regimen from the age of 25,\u201d says Dr Agarwal. \u201cAlso, consume a balanced diet, loaded with antioxidants, proteins and micronutrients as these help repair the internal environment, which cause signs of ageing. Antioxidants also reduce the damage caused by stress and pollutants etc. Sun exposure is the main reason that Indians age so rapidly, so use sunscreens, even when indoors.\u201d Additionally, she recommends using serums with Vitamin C and retinol for normal to oily skin, and \u201cIf you have dry skin, use moisturisers with these plus hyaluronic acid as these ingredients hydrate and prevent ageing. Also, consume at least two to three litres of water daily, as dry skin looks older.\u201d Dr Agarwal adds, \u201cOnce your skin starts to look aged, reversing the damage may require a combination of medical products or cosmeceuticals and aesthetic treatments involving lasers, radiofrequency, botox, dermal fillers and threadlift. We even use these to keep the signs of ageing at bay nowadays.\u201d", "\u2588 When one pops a pimple, the action damages the skin, leading to hyperpigmentation (darkening) and it may even leave a scar", "\u2014 Dr Zubin Mandlewala", "\u2588 Waxing the hair on the face can cause damage to the epidermis or upper layer of skin, and may cause hair follicles to get infected (folliculitis)", "\u2014 Dr Rasya Dixit", "GALLERIES", "View more photos", "Maharashtra vs Karnataka Ranji Day 1", "In Pics: India vs New Zealand 2nd ODI in Pune, New Zealand bats", "Tulsibaug Ganpati", "Pune Celebrates Onam", "Pune festival: Inaugural Function", "Ganesh Chaturthi 2017: Immersion at Pune", "Most Read", "TODAY", "THIS WEEK", "MONTH", "ALL TIME", "Across Pune Mirror >>", "Kapil Sharma's film Firangi stuck at th...", "Kapil Sharma's film Firangi stuck at the censors", "Live Updates: Bigg Boss 11, Episode 54,...", "Live Updates: Bigg Boss 11, Episode 54, Day 54, 24th November 2017 Luxury Budget special: Will Bigg Boss grant points to housemates tonight?", "Deepika Padukone invites 'xXx' co-star ...", "Deepika Padukone invites 'xXx' co-star to India", "Non-Marathi lobby trying to destroy DSK...", "Non-Marathi lobby trying to destroy DSK, says Raj", "The FITE gets real for local techies", "Kin takes on DSK, vows to expose wrongd...", "Kin takes on DSK, vows to expose wrongdoings in the company", "Deepika Padukone invites 'xXx' co-star ...", "Deepika Padukone invites 'xXx' co-star to India", "Kin takes on DSK, vows to expose wrongd...", "Kin takes on DSK, vows to expose wrongdoings in the company", "Kapil Sharma's film Firangi stuck at th...", "Kapil Sharma's film Firangi stuck at the censors", "Amit Thackeray greets workers who went ...", "Amit Thackeray greets workers who went to jail", "Tiger Shroff: Even my father has loved ...", "Tiger Shroff: Even my father has loved my new look", "Salman Khan, Katrina Kaif, Alia Bhatt, ...", "Salman Khan, Katrina Kaif, Alia Bhatt, Sidharth Malhotra to attend IFFI closign ceremony", "Deepika Padukone invites 'xXx' co-star ...", "Deepika Padukone invites 'xXx' co-star to India", "FILM: FASTER FENE", "Tiger Shroff: Even my father has loved ...", "Tiger Shroff: Even my father has loved my new look", "Sinhagad replica to come up at Dhanori", "India vs New Zealand series 2017: Compl...", "India vs New Zealand series 2017: Complete ODI and T20 match sche