ect Portfolio", "Select Asset Class", "Stocks", "MF", "ETF", "Show More", "CREATE PORTFOLIO", "ADD INVESTMENT", "Download ET MARKETS APP", "Get ET Markets in your own language", "DOWNLOAD THE APP NOW", "+91", "CHOOSE LANGUAGE", "ENG", "ENG - English", "HIN - \u0939\u093f\u0928\u094d\u0926\u0940", "GUJ - \u0a97\u0ac1\u0a9c\u0ab0\u0abe\u0aa4\u0ac0", "MAR - \u092e\u0930\u093e\u0920\u0940", "BEN - \u09ac\u09be\u0982\u09b2\u09be", "KAN - \u0c95\u0ca8\u0ccd\u0ca8\u0ca1", "ORI - \u0b13\u0b21\u0b3f\u0b06", "TEL - \u0c24\u0c46\u0c32\u0c41\u0c17\u0c41", "TAM - \u0ba4\u0bae\u0bbf\u0bb4\u0bcd", "Drag according to your convenience", "ET NOW RADIO", "ET NOW", "TIMES NOW", "Digg", "Google Bookmarks", "StumbleUpon", "Reddit", "Newsvine", "Live Bookmarks", "Technorati", "Yahoo Bookmarks", "Blogmarks", "Del.icio.us", "ApnaCircle", "Google Plus", "Pinterest", "I wanted a woman who could get me out of a 3rd-world prison: Jeff Bezos", "ET Bureau", "|", "Updated: Nov 21, 2017, 01.44 PM IST", "0", "Comments", "Bezos and his wife have been letting their kids use sharp knives since they were four, which led them to \u201cwielding power tools\u201d.", "Related", "Bill Gates is losing the world's richest title to Jeff Bezos, thanks to his philanthropy", "Amazon CEO Jeff Bezos's Blue Origin plans to take tourists to space by April 2019", "Fortune of Jeff Bezos spikes $6.6 bn after bumper Amazon results", "The richest man on earth has a sense of humour \u2014 be it about work or family. Turns out, when", "Jeff Bezos", "decided he was ready to settle down, he went on several blind dates, set up by friends. Bezos said he knew he\u2019d found his wife when he met someone truly resourceful.", "\u201cI wanted a woman who could get me out of a third-world prison,\u201d he said in a recent no holds barred interview to", "Mark Bezos", ". Hard not to get candid when your younger brother is the interviewer.", "When it comes to raising kids, resourcefulness ranks high there too. Bezos said that he and his wife let their kids use sharp knives since they were four and soon had them \u201cwielding power tools\u201d, because only if they hurt themselves, they\u2019d learn. \u201c\u2018I\u2019d much rather have kids with nine fingers than a resourceless kid,\u2019 that\u2019s my wife\u2019s perspective.\u201d", "So, how does the billionaire split his time between home and work?", "\u201cI like the phrase \u2018work-life harmony\u2019\u201d, Jeff says. \u201cBalance implies there\u2019s a strict trade-off.\u201d If he feels like he is a productive member of a team at work, \u201cIt makes me better at home. If I\u2019m happy at home, it makes me a better employee, a better boss.\u201d", "0", "Comments", "Want stories like this in your inbox? Sign up for the weekly ET Panache", "newsletter", ".", "You can also follow us on", "Facebook", ",", "Twitter", "and", "LinkedIn", ".", "From Jeff Bezos To Tony Fernandes, Interesting Fantasies Of The To...", "of 6", "Next", "Prev", "Play Slideshow", "Billionaire Dreamland", "16 Nov, 2017", "Jeff Bezos may be minting billions, but he fantasises about being a bartender and making craft cocktails.\n\nA look at some fantasies \u2014 achieved or otherwise \u2014 of other big guns in the business world.", "Role Play", "16 Nov, 2017", "Steve Jobs\n\nThe late Apple co-founder fantasised about celebrating the sale of the millionth iMac by recreating the Willy Wonka golden certificate contest, author Ken Segall wrote in a book about Apple. Jobs even wanted to dress up like Willy Wonka \u2014 the top hat, velvet blazer and bow tie included. He took that fantasy to the grave since California's law required competitions to allow entry without requiring a purchase. Pity. Jobs would have looked cool in a purple suit.", "Martian Earthlings", "16 Nov, 2017", "Elon Musk\n\nReaching Mars is a dream for many, but for Musk, reaching the red planet is just the beginning \u2014 he also wants to see \"a million people live on it\". The tech billionaire's fantasy involves sending people to Mars by 2024 and in a 100 years, having a Martian colony. He has plans for the trip there too. \"Mars is a really nice place to be. The trip has got to be really fun and exciting. There will be zero-gravity games and you can float around. There will also be movies, lecture halls, cabins and a restaurant. It will be really fun to go. You are going to have a great time,\" he once said.", "Bound In Books", "16 Nov, 2017", "Tony Fernandes\n\nThe AirAsia founder shared that it was his dream to see a book about him written. The Malaysia-based businessman said, \"To hear kids saying I have inspired them. It's a nice feeling\u2026 Dreaming is good. Don't let anyone tell you that you can't dream.\" Looks like Fernandes took care of his fantasy himself \u2014 his autobiography was released early last month. The airline entrepreneur also said that starting a no-frills airline was also one of his dreams that became a reality and paved the way for other fantasies to be achieved.", "Voice Of Reason", "16 Nov, 2017", "Mark Zuckerberg\n\nIt was Zuckerberg's fantasy to have an artificial intelligence system in his home that had the voice of actor Morgan Freeman. He spent a year coding a Jarvis-like technology for this, and on a blog post in December last year, shared that the system finally took off. \"I've built a simple AI that I can talk to on my phone and computer, that can control my home, including lights, appliances, music and security and also learn new words and concepts.\"", "Next", "Read more on", "mark bezos", "MacKenzie Bezos", "Jeff Bezos", "Amazon", "Also Read", "For Amazon\u2019s Jeff Bezos, philanthropy is \u2018saved for later\u2019", "Jeff Bezos's fortune hits $100 billion on Black Friday stock surge", "Jeff Bezos sells $1.1 billion Amazon shares with stock at record", "Jeff Bezos passes Bill Gates to become the world's richest person", "Comments", "Add Your Comments", "More From Panache", "1/20", "So, who was Padmavati?", "That was some Thanksgiving! Fake Google ad sends users to scam site", "Can playing football be dangerous to your health in the long run? Science says, yes", "Twisty Board 2 is the kind of fun arcade game that everyone will enjoy", "Umang, the app that allows access Indian Government's services through web and mobile", "In a bid to maintain exclusivity, Chanel will not move to online sales any time soon", "'Coco' review: Pixar's roller coaster-ride of emotions will cast a spell on you", "From FedEx to Dr. Roger Federer: Tennis legend honoured by his home university", "Ruskin Bond gets lifetime achievement award", "Not 007 style! Gin more likely to dampen your spirits than wine, beer", "Thanks to feedback from customers, OnePlus 5T will get a camera upgrade", "First Daughters' Club to the rescue! Ivanka, Chelsea defend Malia Obama", "Desperate efforts under way to save historic McDonald's 'Store No. 1'", "Time to leave the party: Hugh Jackman won't play iconic 'Wolverine' any more", "Privacy issues:\u00a0Twitter admits to revealing location of users without consent", "Engagement soon? No betting on whether Prince Harry will marry Meghan Markle in 2018", "Dwayne Johnson opened up about his struggle with poverty in moving Thanksgiving message", "Film and television industry planning a 15-minute blackout in support of 'Padmavati'", "Solitude for the soul: Spending some 'me time' may reduce depression, anxiety", "Brands pull YouTube ads over comments by paedophiles on videos of children", "Most Read", "Most Shared", "Most Commented", "Elon Musk's break-up with Amber Heard was the reason behind Tesla 3 delay", "OnePlus 5T review: Larger display, bezel-less design, powerful camera make it a strong Android phone", "Trying to get in shape? Cinnamon is the superfood that can help", "Google Pixel 2 XL review: An excellent performing phone with a groundbreaking, brilliant camera", "The art of giving! Our wealth doesn't belong to us, says Nandan Nilekani", "More \u00bb", "Get a Quote", "