", "Insure", "ET Home", "\u203a", "Industry", "\u203a", "Banking/Finance", "04:05 PM | 24 Nov", "market stats", "SENSEX", "33,679", "91.16", "NIFTY 50", "10,390", "40.95", "GOLD (MCX) (Rs/10g.)", "29,376", "-63.00", "USD/INR", "64.69", "0.12", "Sponsored Mutual Funds", "\u2605\u2605\u2605\u2605\u2605", "Returns in %", "DSP BlackRock Opportunities Direct Plan-Growth", "NAV", "\u20b9232.6", "Day Change", "0.89 (0.38%)", "Class:", "Equity", "Category:", "Multi Cap", "1M", "4.63", "6M", "17.34", "1Y", "37.55", "3Y", "17.69", "START SIP", "For regulatory", "disclaimers,", "click here", ".", "Portfolio", "Loading...", "Select Portfolio and Asset Combination for Display on Market Band", "Select Portfolio", "Select Asset Class", "Stocks", "MF", "ETF", "Show More", "CREATE PORTFOLIO", "ADD INVESTMENT", "Download ET MARKETS APP", "Get ET Markets in your own language", "DOWNLOAD THE APP NOW", "+91", "CHOOSE LANGUAGE", "ENG", "ENG - English", "HIN - \u0939\u093f\u0928\u094d\u0926\u0940", "GUJ - \u0a97\u0ac1\u0a9c\u0ab0\u0abe\u0aa4\u0ac0", "MAR - \u092e\u0930\u093e\u0920\u0940", "BEN - \u09ac\u09be\u0982\u09b2\u09be", "KAN - \u0c95\u0ca8\u0ccd\u0ca8\u0ca1", "ORI - \u0b13\u0b21\u0b3f\u0b06", "TEL - \u0c24\u0c46\u0c32\u0c41\u0c17\u0c41", "TAM - \u0ba4\u0bae\u0bbf\u0bb4\u0bcd", "Drag according to your convenience", "ET NOW RADIO", "ET NOW", "TIMES NOW", "Digg", "Google Bookmarks", "StumbleUpon", "Reddit", "Newsvine", "Live Bookmarks", "Technorati", "Yahoo Bookmarks", "Blogmarks", "Del.icio.us", "ApnaCircle", "Google Plus", "Pinterest", "CLSA's Chris Wood remains constructive on India amid banking reforms", "By", "Sanam Mirchandani", ", ET Bureau", "|", "Updated: May 12, 2017, 11.53 AM IST", "0", "Comments", "\u201cThe Indian market could have a sharp correction at any time given that GREED & fear\u2019s long only Asia ex-Japan portfolio, dominated by Indian domestic demand exposure, has gone vertical year to date,\u201d said Wood.", "MUMBAI: India remains the most preferred equity story in the emerging market universe on a ten-year view with the government's renewed focus to adrress asset quality problems in the banking sector strengthening this stance, said", "Christopher Wood", ", CLSA\u2019s Chief Equity Strategist in his widely followed weekly note Greed and Fear.", "However, in the interim, Indian stock market could see a sharp correction given the strong run this year.", "\u201cThe Indian market could have a sharp correction at any time given that GREED & fear\u2019s long only Asia ex-Japan portfolio, dominated by Indian domestic demand exposure, has gone vertical year to date,\u201d said Wood.", "\u201cGREED & fear has found no reason to change the long-term constructive view on this market. Rather that view has been strengthened by evidence that the Modi government is showing a renewed focus to address the one area where it has so far come up short. That is addressing the asset quality problem in the banking sector,\u201d added Wood.", "Last week, President Pranab Mukherjee approved an ordinance to amend the", "Banking Regulation Act", ", giving more powers to the Reserve Bank of India to deal with non-performing assets.", "Wood said he remains constructive on Indian market even though valuations are expensive on a one year forward basis. Nifty has gained 15% and Sensex is up 13.6% so far this year, making them one of the most expensive markets in the Asian region.", "The Nifty trades at 17.5 times on a one-year forward earnings basis, up from 15.4 times at the beginning of this year and a 10-year average of 14.7 times, said Wood.", "Much of this rally has been triggered by strong inflows into domestic equity mutual funds, which Wood says have been a feature since the current government was elected and reflect growing preference for financial assets over traditional assets such as property and gold.", "In", "CLSA", "Asia ex-Japan long only portfolio CLSA has initiated investment in State Bank of India with 3% weighting and added 1 percentage point to its existing investment in HDFC.", "NPA resolution", "Wood said the NPA issue resolution is is the missing link in the Indian macro story.", "\u201cFor once resolved, the way will be clear for the public sector banks to raise capital, a process which should also lead, with the encouragement of both the RBI and the government, to the consolidation of the public sector banks,\u201d said Wood.", "Wood said there is scepticism among Indian fund managers whether such resolutions will happen given the previous failure to address the NPA problem. The stock market also did not react euphorically when the banking amendment law was approved last week, reflecting this scepticism.", "\u201cIf the cynics are proved wrong and the bad debt issue starts to be resolved, it will be a positive for the major \u201cvalue\u201d sector in the Indian stock market. That is, of course, the listed public sector banks,\u201d said Wood.", "GST", "implementation", "The implementation of the Goods and Services Tax this year will also be a \u2018big deal\u2019, said Wood.", "\u201cThere is bound to be some initial chaos which will be duly reported by India\u2019s noisy media. Still, the fundamental point to focus on is that GST will end inter-state barriers to trade. Although the formal rates have not yet been published, the result should be increased tax revenues,\u201d said Wood.", "0", "Comments", "Read more on", "GST", "CLSA", "Christopher Wood", "Banking Regulation Act", "Also Read", "CLSA retains sell rating on Biocon", "CLSA maintains buy rating on Sobha", "Buying GAIL is negative for BPCL: CLSA", "United Spirits gains as CLSA upgrades rating to 'outperform'", "CLSA initiates investment in Indiabulls Ventures", "Comments", "Add Your Comments", "Most Read", "Most Shared", "Most Commented", "Don't buy a new car yet, wait for electric vehicles if you can", "Indian bankruptcies get a dose of karma, Uncle Sam style", "How the egg has gone from leaving you light on your feet to f