he end of Five-Year Plans: All you need to know", ".tt {color: #55ACEE; font-weight: 700;}\n        \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t    .twitter_promo {float: right;clear: right;height: 48px;background-color: #02282D;color: #FFF;line-height: 20px;font-size: 14px;width: 310px;text-align: center; margin: 0 0 13px 13px;}", "In our note for the previous week, we had mentioned about the 10,345 and 10,365 levels acting as important resistance for the Nifty50. During the week gone by, the Nifty50 continued to face resistance at these levels for four out of five sessions and in the end, it attempted to move past it.", "The benchmark Nifty50 ended the week with a net gain of 106 points, or 1.03 per cent. In the coming week, we have the F&O expiry for the current derivative series. We will see the Nifty50 oscillate in a broad range. We might see it inch higher and make an attempt to test its previous high, but a clear-cut fresh breakout may still continue to elude us.", "Despite every marginal higher level that the Nifty50 may attempt, it will continue to remain vulnerable to bouts of profit taking at higher levels.", "Also Read: Market is climbing the mountain of liquidity: What is in store now", "The 10,465 and 10,535 levels will play out as upper resistance area during the coming week. The lower supports that we can expect exist at 10,250 and 10,130 levels.", "The Relative Strength Index or RSI on the weekly chart stood at 66.2680, and it stays neutral for the week without showing any divergence from price. The weekly MACD has remained bullish, as it trades above its signal line.", "No significant formations were observed on the candles. Pattern analysis makes it evident that the Nifty50 still continues to trade in a 22-month-long trading channel that it has created. It faced resistance at the 22-month-old upper trend line at 10,490. However, this resistance has now shifted higher and made some room for the market to attempt marginal highs.", "Going by classical pattern analysis once again, any higher movement that the market may attempt will have no strength, if the lead indicators continue to throw up bearish divergences. Overall, we expect the market to oscillate in a broad range during the coming week.", "Even though the primary trend may not be violated, but in the same breath, we also do not expect the market to race beyond its recent highs. The week may remain largely stock-specific.", "A study of Relative Rotation Graphs or RRG shows the Metal pack may see some individual performance, but it continues to lose momentum and may increase its under-performance against the benchmark, i.e.", "Nifty", "index. Infra, media and IT", "stocks", "may continue to improve their relative performance.", "Some stock-specific outperformance may also be seen in realty and midcap stocks.", "FMCG", "may lag slightly while the", "auto", "pack may continue to consolidate its performance. No major relative outperformance may be expected from services, financial services or bank Nifty during the week ahead.", "Important Note: RRGTM charts show you the relative strength and momentum for a group of stocks. In the above chart, they show relative performance against the Nifty Index and should not be used directly as buy or sell signals.", "(Milan Vaishnav, CMT, MSTA is Consultant Technical Analyst at Gemstone Equity Research & Advisory Services, Vadodara. He can be reached at milan.vaishnav@equityresearch.asia)", "Stay on top of business news with The Economic Times App.", "Download it Now!", "Powered by", "Live Market", "News", "Portfolio", "Mobile", "Live TV", "Biz Listings", "Industry", "Newsletters", "Commodities", "Speed", "Blogs", "RSS", "About Us", "Create Your Own Ad", "Advertise with Us", "Terms of Use & Grievance Redressal", "Privacy policy", "FOLLOW US", "Download it from", "APP STORE", "Download it from", "GOOGLE PLAY", "Download it from", "Windows Store", "Other Times Group news sites", "??????? ??????", "|", "???????? ??????", "|", "Pune Mirror", "|", "B